RUSSIA - Senegal have trashed out of the World Cup following their 1-0 deat to Colombia on Thursday. Senegal bowed out of the tournament despite having equal points with Japan. READ:Â Senegal beat Poland for first African win at 2018 World Cup Both Japan and Senagal finished on 4 points and shared the same goal difference. Japan go through to the last due to Fifa Fair Play rule after receiving 3 yellow cards while Senegal received 6. When the fair play rule is used as a tie breaker, the side with less bookings advances to the next round. Senegal needed a draw to advance to the last 16. eNCA